WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.176
A frequent and highly dangerous misconception exists regarding our co-sell

00:00:04.176 --> 00:00:08.352
agreement: the intuitive but flawed assumption that our sales teams

00:00:08.352 --> 00:00:12.528
are suddenly expected to help sell cloud infrastructure. This feels

00:00:12.528 --> 00:00:16.704
plausible because partnerships often imply mutual reselling. However, the causal

00:00:16.704 --> 00:00:20.880
feature that overturns this is the asymmetry of our products:

00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:25.056
Amazon exists specifically to help us gain distinct sales advantages,

00:00:25.056 --> 00:00:29.232
not the other way around. They brilliantly supply our teams

00:00:29.232 --> 00:00:33.408
with vital account insights regarding internal decision-maker priorities and financial

00:00:33.408 --> 00:00:37.584
contexts, provide unparalleled advocacy by leveraging their standing as trusted

00:00:37.584 --> 00:00:41.760
advisors, and facilitate critical prospect visibility through joint events and

00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:45.936
buyer incentives. Take a moment to internally restate this corrected

00:00:45.936 --> 00:00:50.112
logic: AWS provides sales advantages; we do not sell AWS

00:00:50.112 --> 00:00:54.288
services.
